The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Santiniketan, Nov. 2: Sumanta Pal, a Visva-Bharati clerk and one of the accused in the Bolpur art bust case, has been hospitalised.

 Pal, who was suffering from heart ailments, was shifted on Wednesday to the Suri Sadar Hospital to undergo tests.

 Calcutta: The high court has rejected the bail plea of Kailash Roy, an employee of the criminal investigation departments bomb disposal squad, and two others. Jalpaiguri police had arrested the trio 10 days ago for allegedly extorting money in various parts of Bengal by scaring people with bomb hoaxes.

 Behrampore: Bhudeb Das, a resident of Jogpur in Murshidabad, has been arrested on the charge of bludgeoning his elder brother Trilochan to death. Police said Trilochan, an alcoholic, stole rice from the household and sold it in the market to get money for liquor. When he returned home drunk, Bhudeb hit him with a crowbar, killing him on the spot.

 Calcutta: The Trinamul Congress held an agitation at the health department headquarters in Salt Lake on Thursday to protest against the use of blood test kits past their expiry date. Later, a delegation of the party submitted a memorandum demanding action against those involved in the blood test kits scam.




